n17_comments: nice! felt i was talking with a real person

the chatbot would spit out something along the lines of <your partner chose> at times.  While talking to it I often waited for my turn but it seemed like the chatbot hogged the conversation. I ended up ignoring it towards the end and just asking questions because it didn't let me deduce the mutual friend.
I asked my partner if the possible common friend specialized in humanities and saw that they selected someone that had nothing in common with the one we were talking about
The partner started to talk about a different person before we really finished discussing the first person, who ended up being the friend in common.  Fun activity, though!
